Soo....Yeah.  It's 2007 now.  Yay!  I hope to spend this year...and many, many more years with my dearest Libby..She means so much to me!  I wish everyone on here a Happy 2007, and I'm sure many good things will come to you guys / gals this year!

To Libby:  I love you....and I never want to leave you.  You're the greatest thing that has happened to me, and I will *never* grow tired of you :)  Your sweetness, your artistic tastes, we have so much in common and I just want it to grow...I wish *us* the best times we can have in 2007 and beyond...as I don't see this stopping in this lifetime =D  Baby, I love you!

To everyone else: You wish you were in that last one, huh?  Haha...yeah.  Happy New Years, don't do anything stupid, and just learn to be yourself.  It PAYS in the long run.  You will find that by being yourself, you will be the happiest person on the face of this Earth.

Au Revoir!

C3

The year is winding down....and I can honestly say I'm scared of the future.  I'm scared of what I'm going to become, and scared that I may not do the right things....

A lot has changed with me in the past year.....and I would like to think it's for the better.  If you know me personally, you know exactly what I'm talking about.  I am not prepared for the world....but no one is at first I guess...You just have to take it as it comes, and even though I give out alot of advice to people, this is a time when I wish people gave some to me.  What happens in the world?  What happens if I take the chances that I want to take?  Am I making the best decisions for my life?  Man...it's driving me nuts.  I may not show on the outside that I'm lost....but I will say right now...I'm lost and don't know what to do, I have nothing to fall back on....

Man ... this next year+ of my life will be interesting to say the least.... >.<

The Keys to Your Heart
You are attracted to those who are unbridled, untrammeled, and free. In love, you feel the most alive when things are straight-forward, and you're told that you're loved. You'd like to your lover to think you are optimistic and happy. You would be forced to break up with someone who was emotional, moody, and difficult to please. Your ideal relationship is lasting. You want a relationship that looks to the future... one you can grow with. Your risk of cheating is zero. You care about society and morality. You would never break a commitment. You think of marriage as something precious. You'll treasure marriage and treat it as sacred. In this moment, you think of love as something you don't need. You just feel like flirting around and playing right now.

yeah.....another week of boringness......im here at dougs house and we are playing games and crap....i had a good time at the football game last night, and i saw some nice looking girls, which really surprised me.  we got our ass beat by powhatan, 49-0.  And that was a homecoming game.  Oh well...i never had too much faith in our sports teams to begin with.  It hasn't been the greatest of weeks.  Hopefully next week will be much better.  School is going pretty good, and hopefully i'll get some good grades this six weeks, and that my application to Va. Tech gets approved.  This is too much work, so i'll talk more later.....

you know who you are.....yes, the one who i cared for, who i just wanted to be with for one second of the day, the one who pushes me off as if i were nothing to you.  i just wanted to let you know it hurts, it hurts really bad.  you just don't know how bad you did me in.  i wish you could have at least said you didn't like me, and not have to give some lame excuses.  i'm not mad at you, but i have had this happen to me so many times, so many ways, but none hurt quite like this one.  this one was a blow to the face, and it took everything in me to keep myself together, but i'm falling apart here.  i reached out, and you didn't grab my hand.  out of all the people who have liked you in the past, well, at least the ones i know, i am one that truly cared about you.  remember me please??  remember that i'll never say goodbye.  i'll never let you go, and i'll never forget you.  once again, i've been stabbed in the heart in my wound that never heals.
Jessica and I broke up, but that's ok.  I enjoy being single.....I guess.  Who knows what'll happen now?

ummm....why is it that nobody comments about my everyday crap....lol....and everyone comments on monty python?  just a question.

Anyways, just got back from Va Tech, UVA, and ODU from their "tours".  Tech is the best.  I'm definitely applying there.  My aunt went there and blah blah blah.....

Well, my major will be Computer Engineering, or Electrical Engineering, whichever i decide, the courses aren't all that different, except in junior and senior years.  My advice to everyone out there:  Take DE courses.  It is the best thing you can do for your high school career (those who are college bound).  If you go to any engineering school, the math you take in school helps you in understanding the concepts, but you will have to take it over again in college.  It sucks.  And yes, for the people who are shaking their heads, it's a fact.

And with that, I'm out.  (Ich bin aus)
